latestPosts.caption:
A little about me for all our new friends on here 
Thank you so much for following along 💗

- I turned 35 in August 

- I’m mommy to my 4 year old twin girls, Alaia & Aynara 

-I work as a content creator full time and I also offer  personal style and makeup classes 

- I am mostly an introvert and I recharge by being home with my family 

- My favorite movie is DDLJ (ifkyk) and I’ve watched it over 20 times 

- I used to work in Finance before I worked in fashion 

- I’m a perfectionist but I’m working on being less self critical 

- I hate working out but love living a healthy lifestyle 

-I moved to NYC 5 years ago with my husband after spending over 12 years in the UK 

- I am half Indian half Spanish and grew up in Madrid

-I speak Spanish, English, Hindi and Sindhi

If any of this resonates please follow me I would love for you to join our instafam 💗

Let me tell you something about me…
To be completely honest I don’t event shop that much! I love investing in classic quality pieces that will last me for years and although I’m not super strict about it I have built a capsule wardrobe for each season with investment items that work on rotation and a sprinkle of trends from the high street 

Would you like me to do some posts about how to build a capsule wardrobe? 

Comment below to shop my look 🛍️

Stay toxique ladies ✨🧡 Subtly channeling the new trend for 2024 the Mob Wife Aesthetic. Like many have reported 2024 is going to be moving away from the clean girl look and big hair, more chiseled makeup, bolder accessories and color are all going to be back. 
I love that bolder glamour is back but I’m not one for animal prints and super fitted looks so like with evrything I’m adapting this trend to my own style and I think a mix of #quietluxury and #mobwife is where it’s at for me. What do you think of this trend?

I’m loving how these stunning roman shades by @twopagescurtains have added both function and flair to this romantic and super feminine, pink bathroom. With giant floor-to-ceiling windows, this bathroom is flooded with natural light and I wanted something that wouldn’t block it but would also filter it slightly when the sun is very strong and add some privacy – essential in a bathroom and these shades do exactly that!

We decided to opt for a beautiful ivory linen fabric for a soft and delicate touch and the pastel pink trim adds a lovely decorative detail that ties in with the rest of the color palette and adds that designer feel but thankfully without the designer price tag.

The final reveal of my bedroom and my top tips on how to create a room that feels both calming and indulgent. 

A well-designed bedroom is more than just a place to sleep – it’s a little haven where you can escape when you need a minute to yourself. From soothing color palettes and layered textiles to thoughtful details like the luxurious sofa so I can have a quiet spot to read or work when I need it, or the double layered thermal lined drapery so I can have privacy during the day whilst still letting in the light in but also have a completely dark room with the perfect temperature at night for the best sleep. These elements elevate the space while it making it really functional and that is what true luxury is all about. 

What design elements would you prioritize when creating a restful bedroom? Let me know in the comments
.
.

10 years of US! May you always show me your love helping me set up flowers for my events, spending endless hours choosing cushions and lamps, making me laugh on my never ending cleaning sprees, rolling your eyes when I ask for 1 or 10 more photos to post, opening our ‘VERY’ complicated bed when I fall asleep on the couch and having random dance parties with me and the kids to 90s Bollywood songs, but most of all thank you for being the sanity in my madness and my rock when I crumble 🤍

I still can’t believe it’s been 10 years married to my best friend and 17 years doing life together. We’ve had our fair share of crazy highs and pretty low lows, but I wouldn’t choose to do it with anyone else. Thank you for choosing me and being so persistent all those years ago! You made me see that the words to this song can be true 💗 Love you more than you know 

#10yearanniversary 
.
